# Mojo-Reactor-Glib #

**Mojo::Reactor::Glib** is a Glib-based backend for Mojo::Reactor, which in turn is the basis of Mojo's IOLoop and everything event-based.
This module allows you to use various bits of Mojo(licious) inside a Glib or Gtk based program.

## INSTALLATION ##

To install this module, run the following commands:


```
#!shell

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install
```

## SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION ##

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.


```
#!shell

perldoc Mojo::Reactor::Glib
```

You can also look for information at:

* The source repository: https://bitbucket.org/ralesk/mojo-reactor-glib
* The issue tracker: https://bitbucket.org/ralesk/mojo-reactor-glib/issues
* AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation: http://annocpan.org/dist/Mojo-Reactor-Glib
* CPAN Ratings: http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Mojo-Reactor-Glib
* MetaCPAN: https://metacpan.org/dist/Mojo-Reactor-Glib
* CPAN itself: http://search.cpan.org/dist/Mojo-Reactor-Glib/

